"title": "8749: false teachers",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8749: false teachers",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Those who teach error and in so doing lead others astray. They are to be distinguished from false prophets who are equally condemned in Scripture.</p>\n<h2>The OT prophets warned God's people against being led astray by false teachers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:16\">ISA 9:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:2\">EZK 34:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:12\">ISA 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:20\">ISA 8:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:8\">JER 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:21\">JER 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:1\">JER 23:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:26\">EZK 22:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:7-Mal2:8\">MAL 2:7–2:8</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ condemned false teachers</h2>\n<h3>He opposed legalism and hypocrisy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:19\">MAT 5:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>He identified the teachers of the law and Pharisees as false teachers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:1-Matt23:33\">MAT 23:1–23:33</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:42-Luke11:52\">LUK 11:42–11:52</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:14\">MAT 15:14</a></p>\n<h3>He warned his followers against them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:6\">MAT 16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:12\">MAT 16:12</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:15\">MRK 8:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:1\">LUK 12:1</a></p>\n<h2>The condemnation of false teachers in the early church</h2>\n<h3>Paul urges his readers to avoid false teachers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:3-1Tim6:6\">1TI 6:3–6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:29-Acts20:31\">ACT 20:29–20:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:17-Rom16:18\">ROM 16:17–16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:3-2Cor11:4\">2CO 11:3–11:4</a> <em>The Corinthian church had been undiscerningly tolerant of Jewish deceivers in their midst</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:14\">EPH 4:14</a>COL <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:4\">2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:81\">COL 2:81</a>TI <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:3-Col1:4\">1:3–1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:7\">1TI 1:7</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1-1Tim4:3\">1TI 4:1–4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20-1Tim6:21\">1TI 6:20–6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:10-Titus1:11\">TIT 1:10–1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:9\">HEB 13:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:9-2John1:10\">2JN 1:9–1:10</a>REV <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John2:6\">2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:15\">REV 2:15</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:14\">REV 2:14</a> <em>the followers of Balaam</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:20\">REV 2:20</a></p>\n<h3>Hymenaeus and Philetus are cited as examples of false teachers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:17-2Tim2:18\">2TI 2:17–2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Those who teach will be judged particularly strictly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:1\">JAS 3:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:13-2Cor11:15\">2CO 11:13–11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:6-Gal1:9\">GAL 1:6–1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:10\">GAL 5:10</a></p>",
